# Supabase Storage — Advanced Upload, CDN & Ownership Reference

---

## Upload Limits by Protocol and Plan

| Protocol | Free | Pro | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| Standard REST upload | 50 MB | 50 MB | Hard limit all plans — use TUS or S3 for larger |
| TUS resumable | 5 GB | 500 GB | Correct pattern for >6MB files |
| S3 multipart | 5 GB | 500 GB | Fastest for server-side bulk uploads |
| Netlify serverless body | 4.5 MB | 4.5 MB | Request body limit — bypassed by direct TUS/S3 |

> Rule: Use standard upload only for files under 5MB. Use TUS for browser uploads >5MB.
> Use S3 multipart for server-side bulk imports. Never proxy large files through a Next.js API route.

